Constraint.name: UniqueInstanceName
Constraint.description: Instances of a Component Assembly should have unique names
Constraint.expression: let components = self.modelParts(Component) in\n components->isUnique (i : Component | i.name.trim())

Constraint.name: ImplementationXor
Constraint.description: ComponentImplementation can either be Monolithic or be assembly based, but not both

Constraint.name: PackageConfXor
Constraint.description: A PackageConfiguration can either specialize another PackageConfiguration, or contain a ComponentPackage, or contain a reference to a ComponentPackage

Constraint.name: UniquePackageConfiguration
Constraint.description: PackageConfiguration should be unique within a project
Constraint.expression: let folder = project.allInstancesOf(PackageConfiguration) in\n folder->isUnique (e1 : PackageConfiguration | e1.name)

Constraint.name: UniqueUUID
Constraint.description: UUIDs if defined, should uniquely identify PackageConfigurations
Constraint.expression: let packageconfigs = project.allInstancesOf (PackageConfiguration) in\n self.UUID <> \"\" implies packageconfigs->isUnique (i : PackageConfiguration | i.UUID)

Constraint.name: UniqueUUID
Constraint.description: UUIDs if defined, should uniquely identify ComponentPackages
Constraint.expression: let packages = project.allInstancesOf (ComponentPackage) in\n self.UUID <> \"\" implies packages->isUnique (i : ComponentPackage | i.UUID)

Constraint.name: NoCapacityOrQuantity
Constraint.description: Capability elements cannot have a SatisfierProperty with kind Capacity or Quantity
Constraint.expression: let sp = self.modelParts(SatisfierProperty) in\n sp->forAll (elem : SatisfierProperty | elem.SatisfierPropertyKind <> #Capacity && elem.SatisfierPropertyKind <> #Quantity)

Constraint.name: AtleastOneResourceType
Constraint.description: ResourceType should contain atleast one element

Constraint.name: UniqueGlobalDeclNames
Constraint.description: Declarations at global scope must have unique names unless they are Packages
Constraint.expression: allFileScopeDecls ()->forAll (\n x, y : gme::FCO | x <> y and (not x.isTypeOf (Package) or not y.isTypeOf (Package)) implies x.name <> y.name\n )

Constraint.name: LegalConstantValue
Constraint.description: Constant's value does not match type or is out of range
Constraint.expression:
let x = refersTo () in
 (x.isTypeOf (Boolean) implies ((let y = value.trim ().toInteger () in y = 0 or y = 1) or
 (let z = value.trim ().toUpper () in z = "TRUE" or z = "FALSE"))) and
 (x.isTypeOf (Byte) implies (let y = value.trim ().toInteger () in y >= 0 and y < 256)) and
 (x.isTypeOf (ShortInteger) implies (let y = value.trim ().toInteger () in y > -32769 and y < 32768)) and
 (x.isTypeOf (LongInteger) implies (let y = value.trim ().toInteger () in y > -2147483649 and y < 2147483648)) and
 (x.isTypeOf (RealNumber) implies value.trim ().match ("^\-?[0-9]+\.[0-9]*$")) and
 (x.isTypeOf (Enum) implies x.oclAsType (gme::Model).parts ()->collect (y : gme::FCO | y.name)->exists (z : ocl::String | z = value.trim ()))

Constraint.name: LegalConstantType
Constraint.description: A Constant must be a Boolean, Byte, ShortInteger, LongInteger, RealNumber, String or Enum
Constraint.expression:
let x = refersTo () in
 x.isTypeOf (String) or
 x.isTypeOf (LongInteger) or
 x.isTypeOf (Enum) or
 x.isTypeOf (ShortInteger) or
 x.isTypeOf (RealNumber) or
 x.isTypeOf (Byte) or
 x.isTypeOf (Boolean)

Constraint.name: UniquePackageDeclNames
Constraint.description: Declarations in a Package must have unique names unless they are themselves Packages
Constraint.expression:
parts ()->forAll (
 x, y : gme::FCO | x.name == y.name implies (x == y or
 (x.oclIsTypeOf (Package) and y.oclIsTypeOf (Package)) or
 (x.oclIsTypeOf (gme::Connection) or y.oclIsTypeOf (gme::Connection)))
 )

Constraint.name: UniqueFileIncludes
Constraint.description: A file cannot be included more than once
Constraint.expression: referenceParts (FileRef)->forAll (x, y : gme::Reference | x <> y implies x.refersTo ().name <> y.refersTo ().name)

Constraint.name: LegalDiscriminatorType

 x : gme::Reference | x.refersTo ().isTypeOf (Enum) or

Constraint.name: DefaultCaseCardinality
Constraint.description: A default member cannot have multiple labels
Constraint.expression:
parts (Member)->forAll (
 x : gme::FCO | let labels = x.connectedFCOs ()
 in
 labels->exists (y : gme::Atom | y.name = "default") implies labels->size = 1
)

Constraint.name: ConcreteValueParent
Constraint.description: An abstract ValueDef can have no concrete parent, if it is concrete it can have at most one.
Constraint.expression:
let concrete_parents = 
 self.parts ("Inherits")->select (x : gme::Reference | x.refersTo ().oclAsType (ValueObject).abstract = false)
 in
if (self.abstract = true) then
 concrete_parents->size = 0
else
 concrete_parents->size < 2
endif

endif
